<TEXT>
james k batten chief executive officer 
and board chairman of knightridder inc has been named the 1990 
winner of the william allen white foundation award for journalistic 
merit 
batten is to receive the citation and deliver the annual william 
allen white day address feb 8 at the university of kansas the 
award is named for the late editor of the emporia gazette 
a panel of white foundation trustees chose batten to receive the 
citation which is given annually to a journalist who mirrors white 
in service to profession and country 
not only was william allen white a small town newspaper editor 
in emporia kan but he was also a distinguished newspaperman with 
a national reputation said bill meyer foundation president and 
editor of the marion county kan record jim batten is also a 
distinguished newspaperman with national acclaim deserving of this 
award 
batten 53 directs an international news operation that 
publishes 29 daily newspapers he oversees the companys business 
news and information services cable television operations and 
newsprint production batten also is a director of the associated 
press 
</TEXT>
