an antidrug and alcohol group 
delegation leader levon badalyan president of the european 
association of neurologists said he admires the american concept 
of using the schools to teach young children about drug and alcohol 
abuse he also approves of president bushs attacks on drugs and 
the use of actors athletes and other prominent citizens to 
discourage drug abuse 
he was not impressed by a soviet effort to crack down on 
excessive drinking by raising prices restricting where liquor is 
sold and raising the drinking age for liquor to 21 
the point is that such restrictive measures breed bootlegging 
production of homemade alcohol and worse cases of alcoholism 
appear he said 
the way to overcome alcoholism in my view is through raising 
the general cultural level of society raising it spiritually 
providing a person with specific goals in his life and finally 
impressing on the person that alcoholism is a bad habit he said 
the conference will take badalyan and other delegates to halfway 
houses outpatient clinics and other treatment centers which are 
much smaller than those in the soviet union where the largest 
alcoholism facility has 6000 beds 
