the soviet union for rubles at prices to be determined by the 
soviets romiti said 
because the ruble is not a convertible currency and has little 
value outside the soviet union fiats profits from the venture 
at least in the immediate future must come from exports 
this is an act of faith in a new market which will develop 
with new rules romiti said he added gorbachev will sign an 
agreement thursday that will lay out guarantees for prospective 
italian investors in the soviet union he said the jointventure 
agreement with the soviets also provides for fiat to take its 
profits out of the country a sticking point in earlier business 
talks 
fiat will retain only 30 percent control of the new venture 
with the soviets holding 70 percent but management of the new firm 
wont necessarily be proportional 
