<TEXT>
the transportation department issued 
drugtesting rules tuesday it said are aimed at ensuring accurate 
testing and protecting the privacy of employees in transportation 
industries 
federally mandated drugtesting including random testing 
begins in the aviation railroad marine trucking mass transit 
and pipeline industries next month employees in safetyrelated 
jobs will have to submit to the tests under programs their 
employers must set up 
the departments drugtesting program is to take effect in 
december despite several pending court challenges 
the final rules require employers to use certified laboratories 
and to send three blind samples for each 100 actual samples to 
be tested blind samples are urine specimens that have been spiked 
with drugs to test the laboratorys accuracy 
the rules also call for both initial screening and a 
confirmation test to ensure against false positive results as well 
as a determination by a physician that there is no legitimate 
medical explanation for a positive test result 
employers also may split an employees sample so that a second 
test may be run if the first is questioned 
the department said it rejected suggestions for an expansion of 
the number of drugs for which tests are run 
