stock in the ownership of its employees it envisions an employee 
trust spending 1 billion to add about 5 percent of chevrons 342 
million shares to the 11 percent already held by the companys 
profitsharing plan 
under the esop which will be part of chevrons profit 
sharingsavings plan the company will sell stock to its employees 
and then buy a comparable amount on the open market chevrons 
profit sharing plan holds about 11 percent of the companys 
outstanding stock 
the esop trust will borrow 1 billion from banks and use the 
money to buy newly issued shares of chevron common stock from the 
corporation 
the new shares which are about 5 percent of chevrons 342 
million outstanding shares will be held by the leveraged esop 
trust the company said they will be allocated to employee 
accounts in may when chevron makes its profit sharing distribution 
for the first quarter of 1990 to nonunion employees the plan 
will be offered to union workers through the collective bargaining 
process shushan said 
chevrons stock closed monday at 68 per share on the new york 
stock exchange up 3 the stock has sold as high as 69 in recent 
weeks 
analysts said the rise in chevron stock since takeover 
speculation began is not surprising since the stock has been 
undervalued in recent years chevrons stock has risen about 48 
percent this year 
