chemicals unit had sales in 1988 of 289 billion down from 291 
billion in 1987 earnings last year totaled 18 billion or 517 
a share up about 40 percent from 13 billion or 365 a share 
some analysts say that in a breakup chevrons assets could be 
worth 100 to 125 a share or about 40 billion 
a published report monday suggested that a group of investors 
could be acting in concert to force chevron into a restructuring 
that would boost the stock further 
