<TEXT>
environment ministers from the 12 
european community nations on tuesday approved formation of an 
agency to monitor environmental developments 
the european environment agency should be functional by january 
1991 if it gets final approval from the european parliament said 
carlo ripa di meana the ecs commissioner for the environment 
ripa di meana said the agency would collect and interpret 
standardized environmental statistics from its member states 
the information would be used by the ecs executive commission 
to establish environmental policy for the trade bloc nonec 
countries would be eligible to join the agency but their 
applications would be considered on a casebycase basis 
although no budget has yet been fixed for the agency the 
ministers agreed it would be partly financed by the ecs budget and 
partly by national budgets of its member countries 
the agency would be run by a 14person management board 
consisting of a representative of each ec nation and two commission 
representatives it also would have a nineperson scientific board 
