<TEXT>
an international investment bank has bought the 
carvel ice cream chain from its 83yearold founder tom carvel 
the bank announced tuesday 
investcorp paid more than 80 million for a 99 percent share of 
carvel which is the nations thirdlargest ice cream store chain 
based on annual sales after dairy queen and haagendazs said 
robert glaser a member of investcorps management committee 
the privatelyowned carvel has more than 700 stores mainly in 
new york florida connecticut massachusetts new jersey and other 
east coast states 
tom carvel founded the yonkersbased company in 1934 his 
gravelly voice became familiar to many americans through homey 
longwinded commercials in which he pitches the virtues of 
fancifully named carvel products like fudgie the whale and cookie 
puss ice cream cakes flying saucer ice cream sandwiches and thinny 
thin frozen lowcalorie desserts 
tom carvel will remain a consultant and adviser to the company 
but will not continue making the commercials said glaser 
with the purchase which took effect nov 21 investcorp also 
acquired control of two other food businesses owned by carvel 
nedicks hot dogs and dugans bakery products 
investcorp said it hopes to expand carvels business by 
increasing the number of franchises modernizing its brand image 
and introducing new products 
many of the investments weve made in the past have been good 
companies with good products that would benefit from the injection 
of new capital and new energy said glaser carvel has a good 
name and we want to build on that 
we are confident of carvels future prospects said sanio w 
tung investcorps representative on the carvel board of directors 
in a statement the outlook for the ice cream confectionary 
business is very favorable we anticipate healthy growth of carvel 
in the coming year 
investcorp has offices in bahrain new york and london its 
other corporate investments have included tiffany amp co gucci 
dellwood foods and yacht manufacturers bertram amp trojan 
</TEXT>
